Common.Highlight.Common.Text: High profile Gold Coast Highway location

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
2681 Gold Coast Highway is a two-level building on a high profile corner position of Gold Coast Highway and Elizabeth Avenue, sitting directly opposite The Darling and Star Casino.  

Building features include a secure tenant only basement carpark accessed via Elizabeth Avenue with Council two-hour parking immediately in front of the building and all levels serviced via lift or stairs.  The property is also an easy walk to Oracle and Oasis retail centres and the Broadbeach North light rail station.

The whole of Level One offering has an existing fitout in place with many elements of this fitout being suitable for a range of occupiers.  

We encourage your inspection of this rare whole floor opportunity with secure car parking within the Gold Coast’s most in demand office precinct, Broadbeach.  

To arrange an inspection please contact the exclusive agent.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Located in the heart of Broadbeach

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Oasis embraces an opportunity to connect and evolve a work place that provides A-grade functionality and lifestyle in one of the Gold Coast's most recognised beachside locations. The Oasis has undergone a significant refurbishment program and presents as a modern resort style centre with various breakout areas easily accessed throughout the Broadbeach Mall and at Kurrawa Beach and surrounding parklands.


- Over 21,000sqm of gross lettable area including retail, entertainment, medical and offices
- Range of spaces available from 104sqm to 3000sqm - some with floor to ceiling glass providing panoramic views of the Broadbeach precinct
- Located in the heart of Broadbeach within easy distance to the G:Link light rail station, Gold Coast Convention Centre, The Star and a wide range of retail offering throughout Broadbeach
- Over 1,300 undercover car spaces with two hours free parking for visitors
- A full line Woolworths Supermarket plus 70 specialty stores
- Fibre connectivity
- A dedicated Health and Medical precinct including onsite fitness centre overlooking Kurrawa Beach
- External Restaurant precinct including The Broadbeach, Loose Moose, Elk Espresso and Mario's
- Upper floor occupiers include Australia Post, Ignite Travel, Medical Centre, Allianz and a range of professional service firms.

Current Availability
- Level 1 - 170sqm
- Level 2 - 104sqm and 111sqm

Upcoming Availability 
- Level 2 - up to 3000sqm


Broadbeach is Gold Coast's tightest held office precinct due to its desirable lifestyle and accessibility features and we encourage your inspection of the limited opportunities available.

For more information or to arrange an inspection, please contact the Exclusive Office Leasing Agent, Tania Moore via the links above.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HIGH DEMAND OFFICE LOCATION – ONLY 3 SUITES AVAILABLE

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Gateway entry to the heart of Broadbeach

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Wave is located at a gateway entry into the heart of Broadbeach occupying a high profile corner position on Surf Parade and Victoria Avenue and is easily identified via its signature architectural tower design.

This mixed use development comprises ground level retail, two levels of office suites and a 30-level residential tower above. There is basement parking accessed via Albert Avenue which includes a two-hour free retail customer parking area.

Current occupiers include Starbucks, Koi Restaurant, Crema Espresso, ANZ, AON Insurance and a range of professional service firms and retail operators.

The limited opportunities available for lease include:

Office Suite
- 335.7 sqm fully fitted & some furniture with south facing balcony

Retail Shop
- 345 sqm presented as cold shell with ceiling grid system and internal bathroom. Broadbeach Mall frontage and next door to McDonalds Restaurant.


We encourage your inspection of these opportunities and please do not hesitate to contact the nominated agents below:

Office Suites – Tania Moore.
Retail Shops – Ashleigh Wearne.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Enviable access to first class amenity

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Oracle is one of the Gold Coast’s most desirable lifestyle precincts within the highly sought after beachfront suburb of Broadbeach.  Oracle comprises two residential towers with an eclectic mix of retail shops and restaurants, two levels of commercial suites, on-street and basement parking.  It is a short walk to Kurrawa Beach, The Star, The Oasis Shopping Centre, Pacific Fair, Broadbeach North Light Rail station and is well supported by a range of public transport options.  

Commercial occupiers include – Austereo, AVID Property Group, Destination Gold Coast, Wilson HTM, Oracle Dental and a range of professional service firms. 

Retail occupiers include – Lucky Squires, Bavarian Bier House, No Name Lane Café, Social Eating House & Bar, Mammasan, Chang3 and a range of fashion, restaurant and service retail.

- 315 sqm some beach views, fully fitted & some furniture
- 559 sqm corner position with two sides of natural light, fitout in place

For further information or to arrange an inspection, contact the agent via the links above.

The tenancy sits in the midst of an emerging medical hub with GP Clinic, Chinese Health Centre and Dental Clinic.

- 129 sqm approx
